
* For install :

cd src
mvn clean install


* For import in eclipse :
 just open Eclipse and import existing maven project

== Migrate to maven : 

cd $LENYA/maven_migration/
./migrate.sh


== Test your code : 

* If you need ac related test add this to your pom : 
<dependency>
      <groupId>org.apache.lenya</groupId>
      <artifactId>core.module.ac</artifactId>
      <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
    
     <dependency>
      <groupId>org.apache.lenya</groupId>
      <artifactId>core.module.ac</artifactId>
      <classifier>tests</classifier>
      <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>

* if you need a working publication for your tests, add this to your pom :
<artifactId>core-tests-publication</artifactId>

Make your test extend AbstractTestWithPublicationTest

and call initPublicationTestContent before your tests

{{for creating a mock publication, see also this : 
protected void createMockPublication(String pubId, String area, String proxyUrl)
in :
/core.module.linking/src/test/java/org/apache/lenya/cms/cocoon/transformation/ProxyTransformerTest.java

}}

